<h2>What is Washin Village?</h2>
<p>
  Washin Village is an experience-based glamping retreat in the satoyama (rural hills) of Futtsu City, Chiba Prefecture. Centered around a 200-year-old traditional Japanese farmhouse (kominka), it features architect Kengo Kuma's "Jyubako" mobile houses, Nordic glamping tents, and more.
</p>
<p>
  What makes it truly unique: 16 rescue cats live freely throughout the village. This isn't a cat café — you're staying in the cats' home. It's an experience that simply doesn't exist anywhere else.
</p>

<h2>5 Reasons Washin Village is Unique</h2>
<ol>
  <li><strong>200-year-old authentic farmhouse</strong> — Not a replica. A real traditional Japanese house with 200 years of history.</li>
  <li><strong>24/7 with 16 rescue cats</strong> — The only cat × glamping experience in the Kanto region.</li>
  <li><strong>Authentic Finnish wood-fired sauna</strong> — Real firewood, self-service löyly, cold plunge pool, outdoor relaxation.</li>
  <li><strong>Kengo Kuma × Snow Peak "Jyubako"</strong> — Stay in a mobile house designed by a world-renowned architect.</li>
  <li><strong>Only 80 minutes from Tokyo</strong> — Easy enough for a weekend getaway.</li>
</ol>

